  &quot;What a delightfully treacherous plot unfolds at my very door&quot; he thought. &quot;I shall do this small task and have the very powers of a wizardess to call on&quot;.<br>
  The all too familiar grin forms on his lips. Swallowing the last of his glass of fine red wine, he begins to strap on his armor. The first rays of dawn shine through his window as he sheaths his sword. Quietly he leaves his room and makes his exit of the guildhall.<br>
  &quot; I shall make my way to Neriak, members of the Order can always be found within the walls of my home.&quot; his plan forming in his mind he sets out. Pausing only long enough to summon a minion.<br>
  The shadows of Nektulos forest so fell over Agon as he followed the path that lead to the gates of Neriak. The guards bowed courteously as he entered the city. As his wandered the streets he caught sight of Aphyon, one of the Orders ranking shadow knights.<br>
